"_blank\"></a>:</b></p><a target=\"_blank\"><span></span></a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"p-1 bg-primary col-md-9 col-sm-8 etymology-result\" id=\"etymologyCharacters\">\n        <h3><span></span></h3>\n        <p>There is no known oracle characters found. 没.</p>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span></h3>\n        <p>There is no known bronze characters found. 没.</p>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span></h3>\n        <p>There is no known seal characters found. 没.</p>\n        <hr>\n        <h3><span></span> Liushutong characters (9)</h3>\n        <ul class=\"list-inline list-unstyled\">\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-L27678.png\"></li>\n          <li class=\"text-center\"><img src=\"hanziyan-L38139.png\"></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"yw11\">\n    <h4><span>谔</span>字的基本解释</h4>\n    <div>\n      <p>谔<br>（諤）<br>è<br>正直的说话：謇谔。忠谔。谔谔（直言争辩的样子）。<br><br></p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谔</span>字的汉语字典释义</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>[①]［è］<br>［《廣韻》五各切，入鐸，疑。］<br>亦作“讍1”。“谔1”的繁体字。<br>(1)直言。<br>(2)通“愕”。参见“諤然”。<br>(3)通“岳”。参见“諤諤”。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谔</span>字的康熙字典解释</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>【酉集上】【言字部】　諤； 康熙笔画：16； 页码：<a href=\"https://images.yw11.com/kangxi/1188.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><span>页1188第18</span></a><br>【廣韻】五各切【集韻】【韻會】【正韻】逆各切，?音鄂。【廣雅】諤諤，語也。【玉篇】正直之言也。【史記·商君傳】千人之諾諾，不如一士之諤諤。【家語】湯武以諤諤而昌。　又【廣韻】謇諤，直言也。【後漢·儒林傳】臣無謇諤之節，而有狂瞽之言。　又【韻會】通作鄂。【禮·坊記·鄭註】子於父母尚和順，不用鄂鄂。【釋名】鄂本又作諤。　又通作咢。【前漢·韋賢傳】咢咢黃髮。【師古註】直言也。　【類篇】或作讍。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谔</span>字的源字形</div>\n    <div>\n      <h3>字源演变：</h3><span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">小篆</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">楷体</span></span>\n      <h3>字形对比：</h3><span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">中国大陆宋体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">台湾细明体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">韩国明朝体</span><span><img src=\"yw11-zixing-8C14.gif\">旧字形</span></span>\n    </div>\n    <div><span>谔</span>字的起名意思</div>\n    <div>\n      <p>意为直言。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"yw11_en_transl\">Idiot<br>Basic explanation of words<br>Idiot<br>(谔)<br>è<br>Speak upright: Jian Ye. Loyalty. Ye Ye (the appearance of arguing bluntly).<br>Idiot<br>Chinese dictionary definition of words<br>[①] [è]<br>[\"Guangyun\" has five different cuts, enters the priesthood, and doubts it. ]<br>Also known as \"讍1\". \"谔1\" in traditional characters.<br>(1) Speak bluntly.<br>(2) Through \"stunned\". See \"Ye Ran\".<br>(3) Through \"Yue\". See \"谔谔\".<br>Idiot<br>Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words<br>[You Ji 1] [Words Department] 　谔; Kangxi Strokes: 16; Page Number: Page 1188 Page 18<br>[Guang Yun] Five cuts [Ji Yun] [Yun Hui] [Zheng Yun] Reverse cuts, \"Yin Jae\". [Guangya] Yeah, eloquent. [Jade articles] Words of integrity. 【Historical Records·The Legend of Shang Jun】The promise of a thousand people is not as good as the slander of one person. [Family language] Tang Wu prospered with kindness.　[Guang Yun] Jian Ye, speak bluntly. [The Biography of the Later Han Dynasty] The officials have no feasts, but have wild words.　[Rhyme Club] Tong Zuo E. 【Li·Fang Ji·Zheng Note】The son is still peaceful with his parents, and he doesn’t need hu. [Release name] Huben also made 谔.　It's all over again. [Previous Han Wei Xian Biography] Moisture and yellow hair. [Shigu Note] It's blunt.　【Classes】Or make a mistake.<br>Idiot<br>Source glyph<br>Character evolution: Xiaozhuan<br>Italics<br>Font comparison: Song Ti, Mainland China<br>Taiwan Minutes<br>Korean Ming Dynasty<br>Old glyph<br>Idiot<br>Name meaning<br>Means bluntly.</div>\n</div>\n<div></div>\n<hr>\n<div id=\"bkrs_pinyin\">è</div>\n<div id=\"bkrs_transl\">\n  <div><span class=\"paragraph\">сущ.</span> честная (прямая, нелицеприятная) речь</div>\n  <div><span class=\"example-item\">忠谔 честная и нелицеприятная речь, прямота</span></div>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mdbg.net/chinese/dictionary?p